"Framework" refers collectively to the Mythic Framework ecosystem, including all repositories, modules, libraries, tools, and associated materials released under the Mythic Framework organization.

"Software" refers to any individual repository, module, or component that is part of the Framework, including source code, documentation, configuration files, and assets.

"Licensors" refers to Trey and Mythic Framework as the copyright holders and original authors of the Framework.

"You" refers to any individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted under this License.

"Server" refers to any game server instance operating on the CFX.re platform, including but not limited to FiveM and RedM.

"Module" refers to any standalone or integrated component of the Framework, distributed as part of one or more repositories.

"Redistribution" refers to any act of sharing, publishing, sublicensing, mirroring, or otherwise making the Software available to third parties.

